---
title: Blackened Shrimp & Kale Salad with Roasted Sweet Potato, Cilantro Lime Vinaigrette & Tropical Crema
description: Step aside, side salad—this hearty kale and shrimp mix is the stuff of dinner dreams. Our chef’s tossed together tender kale with sweet pineapple chunks, roasted sweet potato, pickled onion, and a tangy cilantro lime vinaigrette for this hearty-yet-light meal. It’s all topped with blackened shrimp for a dinner you’re going to want to make again and again.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/blackened-shrimp-kale-salad-54380214.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/blackened-shrimp-kale-salad-606471802069ab5fc100f219-6169548b.pdf
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/blackened-shrimp-kale-salad-606471802069ab5fc100f219
cuisine: Caribbean
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 540 kcal
  fat: 29 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 44 g
  sugar: 16 g
  protein: 23 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 900 mg
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}. Zest @lime{1} until you have 2 tsp (4 tsp for 4 servings); quarter lime. Dice @sweet potatoes{1} into ½-inch pieces. Roughly chop @cilantro{¼%ounce}. Drain @pineapple{4%ounce}, reserving juice. Remove and discard any large ribs from @kale{4%ounce}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine half the onion, juice from half the lime, @sugar{½%tsp} (1 tsp for 4), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Set aside to quick-pickle.

Toss sweet potato on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast until browned and tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, whisk together half the cilantro, juice from remaining lime, and @olive oil{2%tablespoon} (4 TBSP for 4 servings).

In a separate small bowl, combine @sour cream{4%tablespoon} and lime zest. Stir in reserved pineapple juice 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water, then pat dry with #paper towels{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add remaining onion. Cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Add shrimp and season with @blackening spice{1%tablespoon} (all for 4 servings), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until shrimp is opaque and cooked through, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Toss kale in a #large bowl{} with a drizzle of oil. Season lightly with @salt{}. Massage kale until leaves soften. Add roasted sweet potato, pineapple, and cilantro lime vinaigrette. Toss to combine.

Divide kale salad between plates or bowls. Top with blackened shrimp mixture. Drizzle with tropical crema.

Garnish with pickled onion (draining first) to taste and remaining cilantro. Serve.